ndgain-id_soci_03-score.def:
Description: A measure of enrolment in tertiary education to represent the education level of a country. It is approximated by the ratio of the enrollment in tertiary education (regardless of age) to the population of the age group that officially corresponds to tertiary education attendance. 
Rationale: Education is considered as an important strategy to build up adaptive capacity and identify adaptation solutions appropriate to local context (Maddison, 2006; Smit & Pilifosova, 2001; Mercer, 2010). In particular, enrolment in secondary or tertiary education is a significant contributor, more than primary education, to adaptive capacity (Tol & Yohe, 2007).
ndgain-id_soci_03-score.name: Education
